===Etymology===
From Japanese [[侍]] ([[さむらい]], samurai).

===Noun===
'''samurai''' (''Plural:'' '''samurai''', ''sometimes'' [[samurais]])

#In feudal [[Japan]], a samurai was a soldier of noble birth who followed the code of [[bushido]] and served a [[daimyo]].

